# Git merge driver configuration for conflict-prone files.
#
# `merge=ours` below is NOT a built-in git driver — it must be registered with
#   git config merge.ours.driver true
# That registration is automated: `npm install` runs the "prepare" script which
# invokes scripts/setup-git-merge-drivers.sh (idempotent, repo-local). Run it
# directly after a fresh clone if you skip npm install:
#   bash scripts/setup-git-merge-drivers.sh
#
# Until the driver is registered, the lines below are a no-op and git falls back
# to the default 3-way merge.
#
# Scope: custom merge drivers run only during LOCAL merge/rebase. GitHub's
# server-side merge button does not execute them, so a stale branch may still be
# reported as conflicting in the UI — but a local rebase auto-resolves these
# files to "ours" instead of leaving conflict markers.
#
# Convention: never hand-merge lockfiles. Re-resolve to ours, then regenerate
# with `npm install` so the lockfile matches package.json.

# Prevent merge conflicts in lockfiles — keep ours (delete and regenerate instead)
package-lock.json merge=ours linguist-generated=true

# Bot-managed on main; feature branches must not touch them
CHANGELOG.md merge=ours
.release-please-manifest.json merge=ours

# Route/barrel files: prefer append-only registration to reduce parallel-feature conflicts
# When two PRs conflict in App.tsx or similar, prefer a human/agent to resolve